 Port Elizabeth - The Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality on Thursday advised residents and businesses in these areas to expect disruptions due to maintenance and repair work at the Lorraine electricity substation on Friday. The repair work will take place between 06:00 in the morning and 06:00 in the evening. All areas fed from Lorraine substation will be affected: Brymore, Glenroy Park, Goldwater, Greenshields Park, Hancorn, Heatherbank, Kragga Kamma Park, Kamma Park, Lorraine, Lorraine Manor, Lovemore Heights, Lovemore Park, Miramar, Overbaakens, Pinelands, Pine Grove, Southmead, Salisbury Park, Springfield, Theescombe, Vikingvale, Willow Glen, Weybridge Park, Woodlands, Walmer Heights, Walmer Downs and surrounding areas. "Only if weather conditions do not only for work to continue, Saturday (26 October) is earmarked as an alternative date," the Metro said. "All electricity installations should be treated as live for the duration of the outage." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  